An unidentified man was found dead on Tuesday in Ramotse village in Temba, north of Pretoria, police said. Temba police spokesperson Constable Herman Moremi said they received an anonymous call about a body next to the road. Police believe the man to be in his early 30s. He was found next to the road with bruises all over the body. His jersey and tekkies were burned next to him. Moremi said the motive for the killing is still unknown and the are no witnesses. A case of murder has been opened and police are appealing to anyone with information to come forward. Anyone who is looking for their relative who is missing, contact Temba saps for arrangements to identify the body at government mortuary, Moremi said African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.